  38. ‌let emit_symbol s =
  39.   for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  40.     let c = s.[i] in
  41.     match c with
  42.       'A'..'Z' | 'a'..'z' | '0'..'9' | '_' | '.' ->
  43.         output_char !output_channel c
  44.     | _ ->
  45.         Printf.fprintf !output_channel "$%02x" (Char.code c)

  48. ‌let emit_string_literal s =
  49.   let last_was_escape = ref false in
  50.   emit_string "\"";
  51.   for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  52.     let c = s.[i] in
  53.     if c >= '0' && c <= '9' then
  54.       if !last_was_escape
  55.       then Printf.fprintf !output_channel "\\%o" (Char.code c)
  56.       else output_char !output_channel c
  57.     else if c >= ' ' && c <= '~' && c <> '"' (* '"' *) && c <> '\\' then begin
  58.       output_char !output_channel c;
  59.       last_was_escape := false
  60.     end else begin
  61.       Printf.fprintf !output_channel "\\%o" (Char.code c);
  62.       last_was_escape := true
  63.     end
  64.   done;
  65.   emit_string "\""

  67. ‌let emit_string_directive directive s =
  68.   let l = String.length s in
  69.   if l = 0 then ()
  70.   else if l < 80 then begin
  71.     emit_string directive;
  72.     emit_string_literal s;
  73.     emit_char '\n'
  74.   end else begin
  75.     let i = ref 0 in
  76.     while !i < l do
  77.       let n = Int.min (l - !i) 80 in
  78.       emit_string directive;
  79.       emit_string_literal (String.sub s !i n);
  80.       emit_char '\n';
  81.       i := !i + n
  82.     done
  83.   end

  85. let emit_bytes_directive directive s =
  86.    let pos = ref 0 in
  87.    for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  88.      if !pos = 0
  89.      then emit_string directive
  90.      else emit_char ',';
  91.      emit_int(Char.code s.[i]);
  92.      incr pos;
  93.      if !pos >= 16 then begin emit_char '\n'; pos := 0 end
  94.    done;
  95.    if !pos > 0 then emit_char '\n'

  192. ‌  let emit_frame fd =
  193.     assert (fd.fd_frame_size land 3 = 0);
  194.     let flags =
  195.       match fd.fd_debuginfo with
  196.       | Dbg_other d | Dbg_raise d ->
  197.         if Debuginfo.is_none d then 0 else 1
  198.       | Dbg_alloc dbgs ->
  199.         if !Clflags.debug &&
  200.            List.exists (fun d ->
  201.              not (Debuginfo.is_none d.Debuginfo.alloc_dbg)) dbgs
  202.         then 3 else 2
  203.     in
  204.     a.efa_code_label fd.fd_lbl;
  205.     efa_16_checked (fd.fd_frame_size + flags);
  206.     efa_16_checked (List.length fd.fd_live_offset);
  207.     List.iter efa_16_checked fd.fd_live_offset;
  208.     begin match fd.fd_debuginfo with
  209.     | _ when flags = 0 ->
  210.       ()
  211.     | Dbg_other dbg ->
  212.       a.efa_align 4;
  213.       a.efa_label_rel (label_debuginfos false dbg) Int32.zero
  214.     | Dbg_raise dbg ->
  215.       a.efa_align 4;
  216.       a.efa_label_rel (label_debuginfos true dbg) Int32.zero
  217.     | Dbg_alloc dbg ->
  218.       assert (List.length dbg < 256);
  219.       a.efa_8 (List.length dbg);
  220.       List.iter (fun Debuginfo.{alloc_words;_} ->
  221.         (* Possible allocations range between 2 and 257 *)
  222.         assert (2 <= alloc_words &&
  223.                 alloc_words - 1 <= Config.max_young_wosize &&
  224.                 Config.max_young_wosize <= 256);
  225.         a.efa_8 (alloc_words - 2)) dbg;
  226.       if flags = 3 then begin
  227.         a.efa_align 4;
  228.         List.iter (fun Debuginfo.{alloc_dbg; _} ->
  229.           if Debuginfo.is_none alloc_dbg then
  230.             a.efa_32 Int32.zero
  231.           else
  232.             a.efa_label_rel (label_debuginfos false alloc_dbg) Int32.zero) dbg
  233.       end
  234.     end;
  235.     a.efa_align Arch.size_addr
  236.   in

  250. ‌  let pack_info fd_raise d has_next =
  251.     let line = Int.min 0xFFFFF d.Debuginfo.dinfo_line
  252.     and char_start = Int.min 0xFF d.Debuginfo.dinfo_char_start
  253.     and char_end = Int.min 0x3FF d.Debuginfo.dinfo_char_end
  254.     and kind = if fd_raise then 1 else 0
  255.     and has_next = if has_next then 1 else 0 in
  256.     Int64.(add (shift_left (of_int line) 44)
  257.              (add (shift_left (of_int char_start) 36)
  258.                 (add (shift_left (of_int char_end) 26)
  259.                    (add (shift_left (of_int kind) 1)
  260.                       (of_int has_next)))))
  261.   in
  262. ‌  let emit_debuginfo (rs, rdbg) lbl =
  263.     (* Due to inlined functions, a single debuginfo may have multiple locations.
  264.        These are represented sequentially in memory (innermost frame first),
  265.        with the low bit of the packed debuginfo being 0 on the last entry. *)
  266.     a.efa_align 4;
  267.     a.efa_def_label lbl;
  268.     let rec emit rs d rest =
  269.       let open Debuginfo in
  270.       let info = pack_info rs d (rest <> []) in
  271.       let defname = Scoped_location.string_of_scopes d.dinfo_scopes in
  272.       a.efa_label_rel
  273.         (label_defname d.dinfo_file defname)
  274.         (Int64.to_int32 info);
  275.       a.efa_32 (Int64.to_int32 (Int64.shift_right info 32));
  276.       match rest with
  277.       | [] -> ()
  278.       | d :: rest -> emit false d rest in
  279.     match rdbg with
  280.     | [] -> assert false
  281.     | d :: rest -> emit rs d rest in
  282.   a.efa_word (List.length !frame_descriptors);
  283.   List.iter emit_frame !frame_descriptors;
  284.   Label_table.iter emit_debuginfo debuginfos;
  285.   Hashtbl.iter emit_filename filenames;
  286.   Hashtbl.iter emit_defname defnames;
  287.   a.efa_align Arch.size_addr;
  288.   frame_descriptors := []

  354.   (ref [] : (string * int) list ref)

  359. (* Reset debug state at beginning of asm file *)
  360. let reset_debug_info () =
  361.   file_pos_nums := [];
  362.   file_pos_num_cnt := 1

  364. (* We only display .file if the file has not been seen before. We
  365.    display .loc for every instruction. *)
  366. let emit_debug_info_gen dbg file_emitter loc_emitter =
  367.   if is_cfi_enabled () &&
  368.     (!Clflags.debug || Config.with_frame_pointers) then begin
  369.     match List.rev dbg with
  370.     | [] -> ()
  371.     | { Debuginfo.dinfo_line = line;
  372.         dinfo_char_start = col;
  373.         dinfo_file = file_name; } :: _ ->
  374.       if line > 0 then begin (* PR#6243 *)
  375.         let file_num =
  376.           try List.assoc file_name !file_pos_nums
  377.           with Not_found ->
  378.             let file_num = !file_pos_num_cnt in
  379.             incr file_pos_num_cnt;
  380.             file_emitter ~file_num ~file_name;
  381.             file_pos_nums := (file_name,file_num) :: !file_pos_nums;
  382.             file_num in
  383.         loc_emitter ~file_num ~line ~col;
  384.       end
  385.   end

  423. ‌type preproc_stack_check_result =
  424.   { max_frame_size : int;

  427. ‌let preproc_stack_check ~fun_body ~frame_size ~trap_size =
  428.   let rec loop (i:Linear.instruction) fs max_fs nontail_flag =
  429.     match i.desc with
  430.       | Lend -> { max_frame_size = max_fs;
  431.                   contains_nontail_calls = nontail_flag}
  432.       | Ladjust_trap_depth { delta_traps } ->
  433.         let s = fs + (trap_size * delta_traps) in
  434.         loop i.next s (max s max_fs) nontail_flag
  435.       | Lpushtrap _ ->
  436.         let s = fs + trap_size in
  437.         loop i.next s (max s max_fs) nontail_flag
  438.       | Lpoptrap ->
  439.         loop i.next (fs - trap_size) max_fs nontail_flag
  440.       | Lop (Istackoffset n) ->
  441.         let s = fs + n in
  442.         loop i.next s (max s max_fs) nontail_flag
  443.       | Lop (Icall_ind | Icall_imm _ ) ->
  444.         loop i.next fs max_fs true
  445.       | Lprologue | Lop _ | Lreloadretaddr | Lreturn | Llabel _
  446.       | Lbranch _ | Lcondbranch _ | Lcondbranch3 _ | Lswitch _
  447.       | Lentertrap | Lraise _ ->
  448.         loop i.next fs max_fs nontail_flag
  449.   in
  450.   loop fun_body frame_size frame_size false
